cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model for online learning, which involves updating the model based on newly observed data. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves matrix computations, which could place it in cs.MM (Mathematical Methods). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of person re-identification, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
